                    <heading>Transport</heading>
                    <dir-section id="AL.DIR.327" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="DIR-SECTREF" usage="ewyb casee">
                         <heading>Railways</heading>
                         <p id="AL.DIR.328">In 2013 the main railway station in the centre of the capital, Tirana, was closed; a replacement station, on the outskirts of the city, opened in 2015. Funding has been approved for the reconstruction of a 120-km railway line linking Vorë and Han i Hotit, on the border with Montenegro, at a projected cost of some €267m. The project is to be largely funded by the European Bank for Reconstruction and Development (EBRD), the European Investment Bank and the European Union’s Western Balkans Investment Framework.</p>
